abstract: Wall Street investors were rattled on Wednesday by the prospect of higher interest rates and new signs that consumers were reluctant to spend again, The New York Times writes.
snippet: Wall Street investors were rattled on Wednesday by the prospect of higher interest rates and new signs that consumers were reluctant to spend again, The New York Times writes.
lead_paragraph: Wall Street investors were rattled on Wednesday by the prospect of higher interest rates and new signs that consumers were reluctant to spend again, The New York Times’s Javier C. Hernandez reported.

headline.main: A Call for Fed to Raise Rates Unsettles Investors
